Advice for a Junior Web Developer
text:
About a year ago, I got laid off from my ten year old job, which was my first full-time job. I worked as webmaster (mostly HTML and CSS), but also did tech support and learned many other things aside from programming. When I was in college, I learned the C programming language, VB.NET, and C# and my approach to programming always was clear to me (my train of thought).

Back to my present situation, I found a job as a junior web developer around 6 months ago, where I have been able to get the rust off my dormant programming skills, but the programming approaches and technologies they use are around 20 years old. I really want to get experience to later on get a job with modern technologies. I've been reading about Typescript, node.js and Angular.

For those with experience on the field, which of these (or other) technologies would you recommend learning for someone like me? Would there be a particular order? Thanks in advance.
